-- Hausner Sees No Problem With Zloty Gain, No Reason for Polish Intervention
-- Monika Rozlal
-- 2010-06-16T08:31:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/hausner-sees-no-problem-with-zloty-gain-no-reason-for-polish-intervention.html

          
          
             There’s no reason for Poland to buy
or sell currency on the market to move the zloty exchange rate,
Jerzy Hausner, a member of the central bank’s rate-setting
Monetary Policy Council, said at a meeting in Warsaw today,
adding that he has “no problem” with the zloty’s
strengthening.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Monika Rozlal in Warsaw at 
 mrozlal@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        